OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMexico Congress votes to   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fkeep military on streets   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Mexico's Congress has voted in favour  
OL,6, of extending the presence of the       
OL,7, military on the streets until 2028.    
OL,9,FTroops have been carrying out public   
OL,10,Fsecurity duties for years as part of   
OL,11,FMexico's war against drugs and the     
OL,12,Fgangs which control their trade.       
OL,14,FBut critics say extending the          
OL,15,Fmilitary's duties for another four     
OL,16,Fyears further militarises the country. 
OL,18,FRights groups say the militarisation of
OL,19,Fpolice duties has led to human rights  
OL,20,Fabuses and further violence.           
